1. hg init -- create a repo in your local disk
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 workspace-z]$mkdir hg-test
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 workspace-z]$cd hg-test
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 hg-test]$hg init
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 hg-test]$ll -a
total 0
drwxr-xr-x  3 caoj7  720748206  102 Apr  9 06:45 .
drwxr-xr-x  5 caoj7  720748206  170 Apr  9 06:44 ..
drwxr-xr-x  5 caoj7  720748206  170 Apr  9 06:45 .hg
--------
you will find a dir named .hg here.

2. hg add -- add files, they won't be actually added until you commit
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 hg-test]$touch first.txt
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 hg-test]$hg add
adding first.txt
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp2 hg-test]$hg status
A first.txt
-------
A denotes Added.

3. hg commit -- save your added file to repo
